'''Faisal Naseem''' (born 20 July 1973) is a [[Maldivians|Maldivian]] politician serving as the [[Vice President of the Maldives|Vice President]]-elect of the [[Maldives]], following the [[Maldivian presidential election, 2018|election]] of [[Ibrahim Mohamed Solih]] on September 23, 2018. He is set to assume office on November 17, 2018, and will succeed the outgoing [[Abdulla Jihad]].<ref>https://www.vancourier.com/maldives-president-concedes-loss-to-opposition-candidate-1.23440343</ref><ref>https://montrealgazette.com/pmn/news-pmn/calm-opposition-leader-wins-maldives-presidency-amid-storm/wcm/9b70d466-d2da-4160-affb-4abdc43da567</ref><ref>https://indianexpress.com/photos/world-news/maldives-election-surprise-victory-for-opposition-leader-solih-5373062/</ref>

